        "ca_dashboard",
        "ocr",
        "oah",
        "district_web"
      ],
      "value": "In this district about 35% of autistic students are in a general-education classroom for most of the day, and about 8.7% are in a fully separate setting. Across all students with disabilities \u2014 a broader group that includes autism along with many other categories \u2014 56% are in general-education classrooms most of the day. On 2024\u201325 state tests, students with disabilities scored about 81 points below standard in English and 176 points below in math, while students overall were 48 and 50 points below. Students with disabilities were suspended at about 8% (compared with 4% for all students)."
    }
